text:
AFL Trades: West Coast close in on Jonathan Giles, Gold Coast eye Matt Rosa Chris Robinson PerthNow AFL Trades: West Coast close in on Jonathan Giles, Gold Coast eye Matt Rosa Chris Robinson PerthNow Yarran headed for Punt Road 1:16 
AFL: Richmond are confident they will be able to strike up a deal with Carlton midfielder Chris Yarran early next week. The Tigers have also recruited Jacob Townsend from GWS. October 16th 2015 a day ago /video/video.news.com.au/Sport/AFL/News/ 
WEST Coast is making progress in its quest to lure out-of-favour ruckman Jonathan Giles away from Essendon. 
The Eagles have targeted Giles to shore up their ruck depth following the exit of Callum Sinclair, who was this week traded to Sydney for Lewis Jetta. 
West Coast football manager Craig Vozzo said the club remained in talks with the Bombers about a potential deal for the 27-year-old. 
“We’ve made some good progressions on his medical and had some good discussions with his management and Essendon,” Vozzo told 6PR. Jonathan Giles battles with Sam Jacobs. Picture: Michael Klein 
“We’d be hopeful something can get done there. But obviously it has to come at the right consideration from our point of view. 
“He knows if it does happen, (it’s) very much as a support ruckman for our two big boys (Nic Naitanui and Scott Lycett) and for Fraser McInnes and Jeremy McGovern, who are probably forward / ruck options. Other Stories
